text: Miskolci Vasutas Sport Club is a Hungarian football club from the town of Miskolc. ==History== Miskolci VSC debuted in the 1958–59 season of the Hungarian League and finished thirteenth. == Name Changes == *1911–1948: Miskolci VSC *1925: merger with Miskolci MÁV Altisztköri Sport Club *1948–1949: Miskolci Vasutas SE (MVSE) *1949–1954: Miskolci Lokomotív SK *1954–1956: Miskolci Törekvés *1956–1993: Miskolci Vasutas Sport Club *1993: merger with Stop FC-Nagycsécs *1993–1994: top-Miskolci VFC *1994–2009: Miskolci Vasutas Sport Club *2009–2011: Miskolci Vasutas Sport Club-MÁV Tiszavas *2011–present: Miskolci Vasutas Sport Club-TS Hungaria == References == ==External links== * Profile Category:Football clubs in Hungary Category:1909 establishments in Hungary
title: Miskolci VSC
